title: S.J. football: St. Augustine hits milestone in win
text:
More coverage: Southeastern Pa. high school sports As for Dobbins, he is 24 yards from the sixth 1,000-yard rushing season in program history.
Jose Tabora threw for 185 yards and rushed for 66 for the Hermits, who are ranked No. 2 in South Jersey by The Inquirer. 
CAPE-ATLANTIC AMERICAN 
Millville 20, Ocean City 13: Will Polhamus connected with Carlton Lawrence for a 67-yard touchdown with 4 minutes, 48 seconds left to send the No. 25 Thunderbolts to the home win. 
NONLEAGUE 
Haddonfield 50 Lindenwold 22: Justin Gallo ran 19 times for 152 yards and four touchdowns as the No. 13 Bulldawgs cruised at home. Tommy Kadar finished 8-of-12 passing for 129 yards and also carried four times for 44 yards and two touchdowns. Haddonfield's defense collected six sacks. 
Cinnaminson 56, Lawrence 28: Frankie Stepnowski carried the ball 12 times for 110 yards and two touchdowns as the 24th-ranked Pirates cruised at home. Shaun Davilla ran for 175 yards, passed for 59 yards, and scored a touchdown both ways. 
Buena 14, Mainland 13: Quadir Albright ran for a 15-yard touchdown with four minutes remaining as the No. 21 Chiefs rallied at home. Mainland led by 10-0 at halftime. Albright ran for a 48-yard touchdown in the third quarter to cut the deficit to three. 
Williamstown 43, Clearview 0: Eric Mercado ran for an 8-yard TD in the first quarter and the visiting, ninth-ranked Braves rolled from there. 
Salem 28, Burlington City 6: Shareef Jefferies threw a pair of touchdowns in the second quarter to give the visitors a 14-0 lead at the break. 
Woodstown 36, Cumberland 7: Zaire Jones finished with 10 carries for 124 yards and two touchdowns to lead the home team. James Parkell ran for 118 rushing yards and a touchdown on 11 carries. Chad Watt had two rushing touchdowns and also made an interception. 
Florence 35, Pitman 0: LaDarius McNeil ran for a 5-yard touchdown in the first quarter to put the visiting team ahead for good. Marcus Crowell recovered a fumble in the end zone for Florence's next score. 
Sterling 42, Haddon Township 7: C.J. Barrett passed for 81 yards and three touchdowns to propel the home team. 
Hopewell Valley 49, Delran 7: Gianni Bryant-Lopez threw for 103 yards and ran for 39, but Delran fell at home.
